Description: In-person and telehealth services offered: primary care, vision care, dental care, WIC, health education. Name: Catholic Charities
Description: Catholic Charities is helping stabilize housing and ease the financial burdens of eligible San Franciscans, regardless of immigration status, through immediate, temporary financial assistance for housing costs such as rent, mortgage payments, security deposits, utilities, and/or HOA and other housing-related fees. Applications may be submitted online at Give2SFhousing.org or by calling Catholic Charities at 415-972-1283 or sending an email to Give2SFCOVID-19@CatholicCharitiesSF.org. The initial application period for these funds will be one-week.

Name: SFMTA
Description: The ETC will subsidize about two to three round trips by taxi per month for older adults (persons 65 and older) and people with disabilities. An older adult or persons with disabilities may apply for the ETC program by calling 311 and mentioning the program.

Name: Disaster Relief Assistance for Immigrants (DRAI)
Description:
Eligibility: undocumented adult, not eligible for federal COVID-19-related assistance, experienced COVID-19-related hardship, and living in California.
One-time state-funded direct relief assistance of $500, with a maximum of $1,000 in assistance per household. The nonprofit organization assigned to each county helps individuals fill out an application and confirm eligibility. Applicants considered on a first come, first served basis until June 30th, 2020.
